---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Navigation from '../../components/Navigation.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="SEF: Social Engineering Assessment Framework"
  description="Structured methodology for social engineering assessments. Combines psychology principles with practical attack simulations. Coming soon."
  canonical="https://snailsploit.com/frameworks/sef"
  ogType="article"
  ogImage="/images/og-sef.png"
  keywords={[
    'social engineering framework',
    'SE assessment methodology',
    'human hacking framework'
  ]}
>
  <Navigation slot="header" />

  <article class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12">
    <header class="mb-12">
      <div class="mb-4">
        <span class="px-4 py-2 text-sm font-mono rounded" style="background-color: var(--color-accent-yellow); color: var(--color-bg);">
          Coming Soon
        </span>
      </div>

      <h1 class="text-5xl md:text-6xl font-bold mb-6 font-mono" style="color: var(--color-accent-cyan);">
        SEF
      </h1>
      <p class="text-2xl mb-4" style="color: var(--color-text-primary);">
        Social Engineering Framework
      </p>
    </header>

    <div class="prose prose-invert prose-lg max-w-none">
      <section class="mb-12">
        <h2 style="color: var(--color-text-primary);">Overview</h2>
        <p>
          The Social Engineering Framework (SEF) is a structured methodology for conducting comprehensive
          social engineering assessments. Built on psychological principles and real-world experience,
          SEF provides a systematic approach to testing and improving human security defenses.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-12">
        <h2 style="color: var(--color-text-primary);">Framework Scope</h2>
        <p>SEF will cover:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Psychological principles underlying social engineering attacks</li>
          <li>Assessment methodology and planning</li>
          <li>Attack vector taxonomy</li>
          <li>Defense strategies and training programs</li>
          <li>Measurement and reporting frameworks</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-12">
        <h2 style="color: var(--color-text-primary);">Related Work</h2>
        <p>
          For more on the psychology behind social engineering, see my book
          <a href="/adversarial-minds">Adversarial Minds: The Anatomy of Social Engineering</a>.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="mb-12">
        <p class="text-sm font-mono" style="color: var(--color-text-muted);">
          This framework is currently in development. Sign up for updates or follow on
          <a href="https://linkedin.com/in/kaiaizen" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">LinkedIn</a>
          to be notified when it's released.
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </article>

  <Footer slot="footer" />
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .prose {
    color: var(--color-text-primary);
  }

  .prose h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    margin-top: 1.5em;
  }

  .prose a {
    color: var(--color-accent-cyan);
  }
</style>
